This paper deals with a deep learning approach for face completion, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of constraints and discriminators, which are common in generative models and adversarial learning, respectively, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a relevant category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pose maps and transformations, which are relevant to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM) applications.
